CORSAIR statement: What memory voltage can be used with Core i7?  The official memory voltage for DDR3 memory is 1.5V. Intel has issued unofficial advice to the market that 1.65V is a good value to keep in mind as a maximum VDIMM for Core i7. However, Intel has also stated that higher voltages can be used without damaging the processor.  When it comes to memory voltage, common sense should prevail - if you run your system for substantial durations at elevated voltage, you will certainly shorten the life of your system.  All of Corsair's Core i7 parts have a specified VDIMM of 1.65v or lower.    Drugače pa gre takoj v oglas  slika  Za koliko bi pa lahko prodal te Corsair Dominator 4GB 1600Mhz cl9 KIT - 1.80V ?
